# Project Structure (UNO C++ Game)

├── BotPlayer.h / BotPlayer.cpp
│                                   Defines the automated opponent. Inherits from Player and overrides playTurn().
│                                   Implements bot logic: prioritizes action/wild cards, then colour/number matches,
│                                   and selects a colour intelligently when playing wild cards.
│
├── Player.h / Player.cpp
│                                   Abstract base class for all players. Stores hand, provides add/remove card
│                                   functions, and declares the pure virtual playTurn() method for polymorphism.
│
├── Card.h / Card.cpp
│                                   Represents a single UNO card. Stores colour/value, provides overloaded
│                                   constructors, ASCII printing, and isPlayable() logic.
│
├── Deck.h / Deck.cpp
│                                   Manages the full 108‑card deck. Builds the deck, shuffles, draws cards,
│                                   and tracks the top card index. May reshuffle discard pile if needed.
│
├── Game.h / Game.cpp
│                                   Core game engine. Reads settings from file, initializes players dynamically,
│                                   manages turn order, direction, discard pile, current colour, and applies
│                                   special card effects (skip, reverse, draw, wild). Checks win conditions.
│
├── UNO.cpp
│                                   Main entry point. Loads configuration (e.g., from deck.txt or settings file),
│                                   creates the Game object, and starts the gameplay loop.
│
├── deck.txt
│                                   File‑based input used to satisfy project requirements. Can store deck data,
│                                   game settings, or other user‑defined configuration.
│
├── UNO.sln / UNO.vcxproj / UNO.vcxproj.filters
│                                                   Visual Studio solution and project files for building and organizing the code.
│
└── .gitignore
                                                    Standard ignore rules for build artifacts, binaries, and temporary files.

# Summary

- **Card / Deck** handle all card data and deck operations.
- **Player / BotPlayer** implement human and AI behaviour using inheritance and polymorphism.
- **Game** controls the full UNO match, turn flow, and special card logic.
- **UNO.cpp** ties everything together and runs the program.
- **deck.txt** provides required file‑based input for configurable game behaviour.
